# Maintained command palette for Meta+k.
# Format: shortcut|description|command
# Notes:
# - Keep this file updated when adding/removing shortcuts in sway/config or Waybar actions.
# - `command` is optional; if empty, the palette only documents the shortcut.

Meta+k|Open this command palette|~/.config/scripts/commands_palette.sh
Meta+Shift+p|Open custom tools fuzzy menu|~/.config/scripts/tools_menu.sh
Meta+Return|Open a Kitty terminal|kitty
Meta+space|Open the Wofi app launcher|wofi --show drun --allow-images --insensitive --matching fuzzy --prompt Apps
Meta+q|Close the focused window|swaymsg kill
Meta+f|Toggle fullscreen for focused window|swaymsg fullscreen toggle
Meta+Shift+space|Toggle floating mode for focused window|swaymsg floating toggle

Meta+Left|Focus the window on the left|swaymsg focus left
Meta+Right|Focus the window on the right|swaymsg focus right
Meta+Up|Focus the window above|swaymsg focus up
Meta+Down|Focus the window below|swaymsg focus down

Meta+Shift+Left|Move focused window to the left|swaymsg move left
Meta+Shift+Right|Move focused window to the right|swaymsg move right
Meta+Shift+Up|Move focused window upward|swaymsg move up
Meta+Shift+Down|Move focused window downward|swaymsg move down

Alt+Tab|Cycle focus to the next window|swaymsg focus next
Alt+Shift+Tab|Cycle focus to the previous window|swaymsg focus prev

Meta+[1..9] (top row)|Switch to workspace by top-row keycode binding|
Meta+Shift+[1..9] (top row)|Send focused window to a top-row workspace|
Meta+KP_[1..9]|Switch to workspace using numpad|
Meta+Shift+KP_[1..9]|Send focused window to numpad workspace|

Meta+Shift+r|Reload Sway configuration|swaymsg reload
Meta+Shift+e|Exit Sway session|swaymsg exit
Meta+l|Lock current session|swaylock -f -c 000000
Ctrl+Alt+Delete|Open session menu (lock/logout/suspend/reboot/poweroff)|~/.config/scripts/session_menu.sh
Print|Capture selected screenshot to ~/Pictures|sh -lc 'mkdir -p "$HOME/Pictures"; grim -g "$(slurp)" "$HOME/Pictures/screenshot-$(date +%F-%T).png"'
Meta+Shift+w|Open wallpaper fuzzy picker|~/.config/scripts/wallpaper_picker.sh

XF86AudioRaiseVolume|Increase output volume by 5%|wpctl set-volume @DEFAULT_AUDIO_SINK@ 5%+
XF86AudioLowerVolume|Decrease output volume by 5%|wpctl set-volume @DEFAULT_AUDIO_SINK@ 5%-
XF86AudioMute|Toggle output mute|wpctl set-mute @DEFAULT_AUDIO_SINK@ toggle
Alt+XF86AudioRaiseVolume|Increase screen brightness by 10%|brightnessctl set +10%
Alt+XF86AudioLowerVolume|Decrease screen brightness by 10%|brightnessctl set 10%-

Waybar click clock|Open calendar popup|~/.config/scripts/calendar_popup.sh
Waybar click audio|Select active audio output|~/.config/scripts/audio_switch_sink.sh
Waybar scroll audio up|Raise output volume|~/.config/scripts/audio_sink_volume_up.sh
Waybar scroll audio down|Lower output volume|~/.config/scripts/audio_sink_volume_down.sh
Waybar click mic|Toggle microphone mute|~/.config/scripts/audio_source_mute.sh
Waybar click layout|Toggle keyboard layout FR/US|~/.config/scripts/layout_toggle.sh
Waybar click notifications|Toggle notification center panel|~/.config/scripts/notification_center_toggle.sh
Waybar click ProtonVPN|Toggle ProtonVPN window|~/.config/scripts/protonvpn_toggle_window.sh
Waybar right-click ProtonVPN|Open session menu|~/.config/scripts/session_menu.sh
Waybar click power|Open power menu panel|~/.config/scripts/power_screen.sh
Waybar click updates|Run system updates|~/.config/scripts/updates_apply.sh
Waybar click disks|Open external disks menu|~/.config/scripts/disks_menu.sh

Setup command|Reload Sway and restart Waybar cleanly|~/.config/scripts/reload_env.sh
